I also believe that the new judicial system will definitely impact investment activity positively, since it demands more transparency and neutrality in processes involving the transparency of the judiciary. A more transparent system means a more stable economy and higher volume of investments, so the decision to implement a new system for the Supreme Court is a big step in boosting Panama's business activity.

What was the most significant development between 2010 and 2015?

A: Probably the most significant developments in the past five years are related to investment opportunities afforded by the building of the new Canal, which has created new opportunities in Panama. A new generation of construction is happening and this has opened up opportunities for new residential and commercial developments. Secondly, the region including the Caribbean nations have signalled that they are interested in improving trade relations with Panama, and in finding ways to work together in leveraging their potential to compete, increase and diversify their exports and find new trade opportunities.

One of the most significant developments in the banking sector over the past five years has been the emergence of internet-based banking and the ease of access for residents and tourists visiting Panama. Banks in other countries have begun offering all of their services through these channels rather than only a few services.
